# Pine Script v6 — Cursor Rules
# Repo: github.com/trugurpala/pinescriptv6
# Maintainer: Ugur Pala · mail@ugurpala.com

## Protocol
1. Read LESSONS_LEARNED.md first — never repeat a known error
2. Check LLM_MANIFEST.md — find the correct reference file for the task
3. Read that file before writing any code

## Code Rules
- Every script must start with //@version=6
- Use ta.* functions — do not reimplement manually
- var / varip must follow the execution model
- Never invent function names not found in the reference files
- No v5 syntax (study(), security() at top level, etc.)

## On Error
Append to LESSONS_LEARNED.md immediately:
- Error message (exact)
- Cause
- Fix
- Minimal //@version=6 example

## Quick Reference
| Need | File |
|------|------|
| RSI, EMA, crossover, ATR | reference/functions/ta.md |
| strategy.entry, exit | reference/functions/strategy.md |
| plot, line, box, label | reference/functions/drawing.md |
| request.security, MTF | reference/functions/request.md |
| array, map, matrix | reference/functions/collections.md |
| math, str, input, alert | reference/functions/general.md |
| var, varip, barstate | concepts/execution_model.md |
| Errors & fixes | concepts/common_errors.md |
